* Boot OPENTHOS in DEBUG mode

* Disable surfaceflinger: modify /init.rc like, then exit

  diff --git a/rootdir/init.rc b/rootdir/init.rc
index dc20052..32e9661 100644
--- a/rootdir/init.rc
+++ b/rootdir/init.rc
@@ -562,6 +562,7 @@ service surfaceflinger /system/bin/surfaceflinger
 #   user system
     group graphics drmrpc
     onrestart restart zygote
+    disabled
 
 service drm /system/bin/drmserver
     class main

* Enable network: netcfg eth0 dhcp, check the ip by ifconfig eth0

* It's strange using 'adb connect ip'? To workaround it, I use the ssh port forward method:
  - Open another VT: openvt, switch to Alt-F4

  - ssh cwhuang@10.0.1.1 -R 5556:127.0.0.1:5555
    where 10.0.1.1 is my Linux debug host

* On the Linux host 10.0.1.1, connect to port 5556:
  - adb connect 127.0.0.1:5556
  - adb logcat -v threadtime

* Start surfaceflinger manually
  - Switch to VT1 (Alt-F1) on the OPENTHOS device
  - start surfaceflinger
